A secondary carboxamide resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of [(2R,6S)-2,6-dimethylmorpholin-4-yl]acetic acid with the amino group of 2-(7-amino-9H-thioxanthen-4-yl)-6-(morpholin-4-yl)-4H-pyran-4-one. It is an ATM kinase inhibitor (IC50 = 6.3 nM).
A fatty acid with a hydroxy group at a position undefined. R1 and R2 are carbon chains with undefined number of carbons, unsaturations or branching. Major microspecies at pH 7.3
A member of the class of thianthrenes that is thianthrene substituted by a 6-(morpholin-4-yl)-4-oxo-4H-pyran-2-yl group at position 1. It is potent inhibitor of ATM kinase.
A member of the class of thianthrenes that is thianthrene substituted by a 4-oxo-6-(piperidin-1-yl)-4H-pyran-2-yl group at position 1. It is a weakly active inhibitor of ATM kinase.
A 4-azidophenylalanine that has L-configuration. It is used as a bioorthogonal click-chemistry reagent.

A member of the class of quinazolines that is 1-methylquinazoline-2,4(1H,3H)-dione substituted by 2,6-dimethylphenyl and 2-hydroxy-6-oxocyclohex-1-ene-1-carbonyl groups at positions 3 and 6, respectively. It is a HPPD inhibitor and a selective herbicide used for the weed control in Sorghum crops.

A tertiary carboxamide resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of 3-(difluoromethyl)-5-fluoro-1-methyl-1H-pyrazole-4-carboxylic acid with the amino group of N-[5-chloro-2-(propan-2-yl)benzyl]cyclopropanamine. It is a broad spectrum fungicide developed by Bayer that exhibits high efficacy against the major fungal diseases of cereal crops (wheat, triticale, rye, barley and oats).
